<ActivityLayout
  title="Hilltop Villages — Activities near Mas du Chanoine"
  description="Hilltop Villages: discover this activity near our guesthouse on the French Riviera."
  lang="en"
  activityName="Hilltop Villages"
  breadcrumb={[
    { label: "Home", href: "/en/" },
    { label: "Activities", href: "/en/activities-french-riviera/" },
    { label: "Hilltop Villages" }
  ]}
  image={{ src: "/media/activites/villages-perches.jpg", alt: "Hilltop Villages" }}
  backLabel="← All activities"
  backUrl="/en/activities-french-riviera/"
  bookingLabel="Book Now"
  alternates={{ fr: "/activites/visiter-les-villages-perches/", en: "/en/activites/hilltop-villages/", it: "/it/activites/i-villaggi-collinari/" }}
>
  <p>The Alps take their rise in the Nice hinterland. The most remarkable perched villages from West to East are: Gourdon, Tourrettes-sur-Loup and Eze.</p>
  <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-semibold text-primary-900 mt-6 mb-2">Gourdon</h3>
  <p>The village is perched on the rock 760 meters up to sea, above the Vallée du Loup. Only 10 km far from the Mediterranean Sea, it offers a unique panorama on the French Riviera from Nice to Théoule, more than 80km.</p>
  <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-semibold text-primary-900 mt-6 mb-2">Tourrettes-sur-Loup</h3>
  <p>A medieval village nicknamed the City of Violets. Twenty workshops and craftmen's shops open their doors to you.</p>
  <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-semibold text-primary-900 mt-6 mb-2">Eze</h3>
  <p>Built at the top of a cliff, overlooking Saint-Jean-Cap-Ferrat, the village of Eze offers many hidden treasures. Arrived at the top, you will see the Exotic Garden with hundreds of succulents and cacti.</p>
</ActivityLayout>
